# 🌐 2. Networking Demo – No Internet on Wi‑Fi

## 🎯 Scenario
User reports:
> “Wi‑Fi says connected but I can’t access the internet.”

## 🔧 Troubleshooting Steps (Demo)
1. Run:
ipconfig /all
→ APIPA address (169.254.x.x)  
2. Restart router  
3. Forget and reconnect to Wi‑Fi  
4. Renew IP:
ipconfig /release
ipconfig /renew
5. Test DNS:
nslookup google.com

## 📝 Model Ticket Note
User receiving APIPA address due to DHCP failure. Restarted router and renewed IP. Device obtained valid address and internet restored. Issue resolved.

